HEADWORD: Antelucan
<hw>An`te*lu"can</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>antelucanus</ets>; <ets>ante</ets> + <ets>lux</ets> light.]</ety>
<def>Held or being before light; -- a word applied to assemblies of
Christians, in ancient times of persecution, held before light in the
morning.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Antelucan</xex> worship.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>De
Quincey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

